  "concept": "vuejs/core#11474: shallowReadonly assignment, no type error prompt",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:22:26.421243+00:00",
  "text": "shallowReadonly assignment, no type error prompt\n\n### Vue version\n\nv3.5.0-alpha.5\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n\nhttps://play.vuejs.org/#\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nhttps://play.vuejs.org/#\n\n### What is expected?\n\n```vue\r\n<script setup>\r\nimport { ref , readonly,shallowReadonly} from 'vue'\r\n\r\nconst foo = readonly(new Map())\r\n//ts-error: Property 'set' does not exist on type 'ReadonlyMap<any, any>'.ts(2339)\r\nfoo.set('a',1) \r\n\r\n\r\nconst bar = shallowReadonly(new Map())\r\n//ts-error: Property 'set' does not exist on type 'ReadonlyMap<any, any>'.ts(2339)\r\nbar.set('a',2)\r\n</script>\r\n\r\n\r\n```\n\n### What is actually happening?\n\n```vue\r\n<script setup>\r\nimport { ref , readonly,shallowReadonly} from 'vue'\r\n\r\nconst foo = readonly(new Map())\r\n//ts-error: Property 'set' does not exist on type 'ReadonlyMap<any, any>'.ts(2339)\r\nfoo.set('a',1) \r\n\r\n\r\nconst bar = shallowReadonly(new Map())\r\nbar.set('a',2) // no error message\r\n</script>\r\n\r\n\r\n```\n\n### System Info\n\n_No response_\n\n### Any additional comments?\n\n_No response_",
  "language": "en",
